<body>
  <header>
    <h1>CON 502 – Prompt Engineering Activities</h1>
    <p>Use these prompts during class. You can copy and paste them into ChatGPT, Gemini, etc.</p>
  </header>

  <main>
    <!-- Activity 1: Keyword Generation -->
    <section class="activity">
      <h2>Activity 1 – Keyword Generation (Zero-shot)</h2>
      <p>Use this prompt with your own research topic to generate keywords and Boolean strings.</p>
      <textarea id="prompt1" readonly>
Generate a list of keywords and synonyms for the topic &lt;insert your topic here&gt;. Include:
- Main keywords
- Synonyms or related terms
- Technical terms used in construction management (or my field)
- Broader terms
- Narrower terms

Then produce three example Boolean search strings that I could use in databases like Scopus, Web of Science, or Google Scholar.</textarea>
      <div>
        <button class="copy-btn" data-target="prompt1">Copy prompt</button>
        <span class="status" id="status1"></span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Activity 2: Structured Summaries -->
    <section class="activity">
      <h2>Activity 2 – Structured Literature Summaries (Few-shot)</h2>
      <p>First paste one example abstract and its structured summary. Then use this pattern for a new abstract.</p>
      <textarea id="prompt2" readonly>
Here is an example of a structured summary format I want you to follow:

- Research Problem:
- Methods Used:
- Project Context / Setting:
- Key Findings:
- Practical Implications for Construction Management:

Using the structure shown above, summarize the following construction management article abstract in the same style and format:

&lt;paste abstract here&gt;</textarea>
      <div>
        <button class="copy-btn" data-target="prompt2">Copy prompt</button>
        <span class="status" id="status2"></span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Activity 3: Role Prompting – Expert Feedback -->
    <section class="activity">
      <h2>Activity 3 – Expert Feedback on Research Questions (Role prompting)</h2>
      <p>Use this to get critique on your research question from an “expert”. Replace the role and question with your own.</p>
      <textarea id="prompt3" readonly>
Act as a [construction safety researcher / sustainability expert / construction management researcher].

Here are the research question(s) I would like you to evaluate:
&lt;insert your research question(s) here&gt;

Provide an expert critique focusing on:
- Clarity and specificity
- Feasibility in realistic research settings
- Alignment with current research gaps
- Suggested improvements or alternative questions

Then rewrite the research question(s) in a clearer and more feasible form.</textarea>
      <div>
        <button class="copy-btn" data-target="prompt3">Copy prompt</button>
        <span class="status" id="status3"></span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Activity 4: Contextual Prompting – Research Design -->
    <section class="activity">
      <h2>Activity 4 – Contextual Prompting for Research Design</h2>
      <p>Use this to get suggestions for data collection and methods based on a short project context.</p>
      <textarea id="prompt4" readonly>
Here is the context for my study:
&lt;insert 2–4 sentences describing the project or topic context&gt;

My research question(s) is/are:
&lt;insert your research question(s) here&gt;

Based on this context, please suggest:
- Possible data collection methods
- Key variables to consider
- Suitable analytical or statistical methods

Then summarize a refined research approach that fits this context.</textarea>
      <div>
        <button class="copy-btn" data-target="prompt4">Copy prompt</button>
        <span class="status" id="status4"></span>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <script>
    function copyPrompt(targetId, statusId) {
      const textarea = document.getElementById(targetId);
      const status = document.getElementById(statusId);
      const button = document.querySelector('button[data-target="' + targetId + '"]');

      if (!textarea) return;

      navigator.clipboard.writeText(textarea.value)
        .then(() => {
          status.textContent = "Copied!";
          button.disabled = true;
          setTimeout(() => {
            status.textContent = "";
            button.disabled = false;
          }, 1500);
        })
        .catch(() => {
          status.textContent = "Copy failed. Please select and copy manually.";
        });
    }

    document.querySelectorAll(".copy-btn").forEach((btn, index) => {
      btn.addEventListener("click", () => {
        const target = btn.getAttribute("data-target");
        copyPrompt(target, "status" + (index + 1));
      });
    });
  </script>
